  "bio": [
    "Manuel Puig Rocha is the largest individual shareholder of Puig Brands, a fashion and beauty conglomerate which owns Nina Ricci, Carolina Herrera and Charlotte Tilbury.",
    "The company was founded by his grandfather Antonio Puig in 1914, who got his big break with the Milady Lipstick in 1922.",
    "Rocha has been vice president of Puig Brands since 2007, responsible for overseeing its international subsidiaries.",
    "Rocha's father, Antonio, along with his three uncles Mariano, José María and Enrique joined the company in 1950 and helped bolster its growth.",
    "Today at least 14 family members control Puig Brands."
